# Phase 215.J.4 — board Kconfig overlay: enable RUST_SUPPORTED for the FVP
# Base_RevC AEMv8-R board WITHOUT mutating the consumer's zephyr-lang-rust tree.
#
# `zephyr-lang-rust` declares `config RUST_SUPPORTED` as a typeless-prompt bool
# whose only `default y if (...)` covers Cortex-M / RISC-V / 64-bit ARCH_POSIX
# — none of which match this board's AArch64 AEMv8-R (Cortex-R) core, so
# `RUST_SUPPORTED` defaults n and `CONFIG_RUST=y` is silently dropped.
#
# Kconfig allows a symbol's properties to be defined across multiple files; the
# first `default` whose condition is satisfied (in parse order) wins. Since the
# upstream condition is false on this board, the board-keyed default below is
# the one that fires — a non-destructive cross-file extension. Restating `bool`
# keeps the symbol well-typed regardless of which module Kconfig parses first.
#
# This handles only the RUST_SUPPORTED symbol; the lang-rust CMake
# `_rust_map_target` → `aarch64-unknown-none` mapping is supplied separately by
# scripts/zephyr/aarch64-rust-patch.sh (Phase 215.J.2 step (b)).

config RUST_SUPPORTED
	bool
	default y if BOARD_FVP_BASER_AEMV8R
